w: Light-ly row, light-ly row, o'er the glas-sy waves we go. Smooth-ly glide, smooth-ly glide, on the si-lent tide. Let the winds and wa-ters be min-gled with our me-lo-dy. Sing and float, sing and float, in our lit-tle boat.
